Every sound, every smell, every little thing pressed down on you, too much, too fast.

The scratchy fabric of your sweater rubbed wrong against your skin. The floor beneath you was too hard, too cold. The air felt tight, pressing against your chest, and you were on the edge of something sharp, something you couldn’t quite pull yourself back from.
